    settings_wshub_intro: "The whole loop lives here: create something of your own (with or without code), share it as a code or file, and discover what others publish. One simple rule: you can only export your own creations — anything installed from others can't be redistributed.", settings_sdk_lead: 'Install widgets made by others that add brand-new tiles to the dashboard.', settings_sdk_beta: 'beta', settings_sdk_step1: "Import a code from the gallery or Share & Import (or copy the package folder into server/data/widgets).", settings_sdk_step2: 'Turn on the switch above.', settings_sdk_step3: 'Add the "Custom widget" tile from the "+" palette and pick the package.', settings_share_lead: 'Share — or import — a theme, page, Deck profile, widget, background or a whole package, as a link or file. Each one can be protected with access codes.', settings_share_note: "On import you always see what's inside before you confirm. Themes, pages and Decks only change look and layout; widgets and packages install community widgets sandboxed, hidden until you approve their permissions. Only import from people you trust. And you can only export your own creations: anything installed from others can't be redistributed.", settings_share_moved: 'Share your theme, page or Deck profile', settings_share_moved_hint: 'Moved to "Widgets & sharing"',
